  <static seed="15" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring25.pg">
    <statement><p>Find the greatest common factor of the following terms.</p>
<p><m>{10r^{10}}</m>, <m>{-100r^{9}}</m>, <m>{50r^{7}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>10r^{7}\hbox{ or }-10r^{7}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>There are two things to look for in this problem:
<ul label="disc">
<li>
<p>the greatest common <em>numerical</em> factor is <m>10</m></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the greatest common <em>algebraic</em> factor is <m>r^{7}</m>, since it hase the <em>lowest</em> exponent.</p>
</li>
</ul></p>
<p>The greatest common factor of <m>{10r^{10}}</m>, <m>{-100r^{9}}</m> and <m>{50r^{7}}</m> is <m>{10r^{7}\hbox{ or }-10r^{7}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
